		<div class="post" id="post-2812788">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2812788)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2812788">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kenneth1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1813809); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1813809&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182720" alt="kenneth1221" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1813809)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kenneth1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1813809); return false;" >kenneth1221</a></span> <span class="odate time_1494094493 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 May 2017 18:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2812788">
									

<p>An SPC based on <a href="/scp-1258">SCP-1258</a>. CYAN ABYSS, or Sharkics, were first mentioned in <a href="/spc-140">SPC-140</a>.</p>
<p>I owe a lot to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1494096565" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1494096565" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;">sirpudding</a></span> for helping me change this into its current form. The first few drafts were different, to say the least. <em>The Laundry Files</em>, by Charles Stross, was also an inspiration as supernatural spy fiction.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A big complaint about previous articles in the SPC format was that they simply didn't do enough. They were, in a word, often too derivative of the SCPs on which they were based. My own work, <a href="/spc-1981">SPC-1981</a>, is certainly guilty of this, and I highly plan on revisiting it.<br />
This was an attempt to avoid that from the get-go. When I first started writing this piece, I knew that I wanted to include a certain level of oceanic political intrigue. From there on, the worldbuilding crystallized. Thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1494096565" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;">sirpudding</a></span> for a lot of useful advice on this stage.</p>
<p>More (possibly) coming later!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

