					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mlister" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3027978); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3027978&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182720" alt="mlister" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3027978)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mlister" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3027978); return false;" >mlister</a></span> <span class="odate time_1494108396 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 May 2017 22:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2812971">
									

<p>The idea of the Centre teaching dolphins how to karate sharks is great&#8230; but the SPC fails to live up to the premise. Rather than embracing the absurdity of it all, or having reality destroy the plan in amusing ways, you take the plunge into some world-building that I frankly don't find interesting. The interview log was a highlight for me in how it balances the grimdarkness and silliness to be both funny and sincerely dark, but it couldn't save the article.</p>
<p>-1</p>

