		<div class="post" id="post-2813000">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2813000)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2813000">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kenneth1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1813809); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1813809&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182720" alt="kenneth1221" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1813809)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kenneth1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1813809); return false;" >kenneth1221</a></span> <span class="odate time_1494110365 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 May 2017 22:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2813000">
									

<p>I get where you're coming from on all counts. The piece is long and goes really heavily into the worldbuilding of the SPC, though I personally intended to let the report act as a straight man to the inherent absurdity of the concept. I think the world itself is absurd enough to simply be described.</p>
<p>I would like to explain my choice to go down such a worldbuilding heavy route, for the record. Unlike the Foundation, the Centre has very little widely accepted background. My other attempt, at SPC-1981, is kind of&#8230; <em>shallow</em>. It didn't have enough differentiation within the SPC and was too similar to the SCP. The original version of this SPC had the dolphins rebelling, attacking Japan, and then coming back when they realized how f**d up the world was. It was fun to write, but predictable, and I'm not sure I could've done much with the antics of dolphins without falling into a rut.</p>
<p>Since CYAN ABYSS had already been established in SPC-140 as the predominant oceanic civilization, using them would help create a more cohesive Centreverse and give the Centre a target to actually deploy militarized punching dolphins against.</p>
<p>Ultimately, I hope to strike a better balance between worldbuilding and absurdity in future SPCs.</p>

							</div>

								
					
