			<div class="content" id="post-content-2814556">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Sharks are fish.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Fish&quot; is paraphyletic. <em>You</em> are as closely related to a salmon as a dogfish is. Either all vertebrates are fish or none are, cladistically.</p>
<p>You can say that sharks are cartilaginous fishes though.</p>
<p>Orcas are <em>definitely</em> mammals with placental live births, endothermy, hair, and milk. They share a recent commonly ancestors with all other cetaceans, and are reasonably closely related to the hippopotamus.</p>

